README.md

license

   [https://getcomposer.org/][logo-composer-transparent.png]

     A curated list of resources for Composer, Packagist, Satis, Plugins,
     Scripts, Videos, Tutorials.

   You might also like [https://github.com/ziadoz/awesome-php]awesome-php.

   Please read the
   c
   ontribution guidelines before contributing.

Composer

     * [https://getcomposer.org/]Official Website
     * [https://github.com/composer/composer/issues]Issues
     * [https://github.com/composer/composer]Github
     * [https://getcomposer.org/doc/00-intro.md]Getting Started Guide and
       Installation Instructions
     * [https://getcomposer.org/doc/]Documentation
     * [https://getcomposer.org/apidoc/master/index.html]API Documentation
     * [https://packagist.org/]Find Packages on Packagist
     * [http://composer.json.jolicode.com/]CheatSheet - Overview of CLI
       commands and composer.json schema.
     * [https://github.com/composer/installers]Composer Installers -
       Composer installers for multiple frameworks.

Support

Stack Overflow

     * You might use the following tags: composer-php, packagist, satis +
       php.
     * [http://stackoverflow.com/questions/ask?tags=composer-php+php]Ask a
       new question
     * [http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/composer-php]Find
       questions tagged composer-php

IRC

     * IRC channels are on irc.freenode.org:
       [https://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=composer]#composer for
       users and
       [https://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=composer-dev]#composer-dev
       for development.

Plugins

     * [https://getcomposer.org/doc/articles/plugins.md]Documentation for
       Plugins - This offical documentation is good starting point, when
       writing a Composer plugin.
     * [https://github.com/fxpio/composer-asset-plugin]Composer-Asset-Plug
       in - A npm/Bower Dependencies Manager for Composer.
     * [https://github.com/naderman/composer-aws]Composer-AWS - The plugin
       loads repository data and downloads packages from Amazon S3 (with
       authentication support for private repositories).
     * [https://github.com/bamarni/composition]Composer-Composition -
       Provides an API, for checking your environment at runtime.
     * [https://github.com/nfreear/composer-suggest]Composer-Suggest -
       Enables you to install a custom group of suggested packages, based
       on keyword patterns.
     * [https://github.com/Soullivaneuh/composer-versions-check]Composer-V
       ersions-Check - Shows outdated packages from last major versions
       after using the update command (showing "Latest is vX.Y.Z").
     * [https://github.com/pyrech/composer-changelogs]Composer-Changelogs
       - Provides a summary of the updates with links to
       changelog/releasenote/tag. The output is ready to be pasted into
       the commit message when updating the composer.lock file.
     * [https://github.com/wikimedia/composer-merge-plugin]Composer-Merge-
       Plugin - Merges multiple composer.json files at Composer runtime.
     * [https://github.com/bamarni/composer-bin-plugin]Composer-Bin-Plugin
       - Adds support for managing dependencies for multiple packages in a
       single repository or isolate bin dependencies.
     * [https://github.com/theofidry/composer-inheritance-plugin]Composer-
       Inheritance-Plugin - Opinionated version of Wikimedia
       composer-merge-plugin to work in pair with Bamarni
       composer-bin-plugin.
     * [https://github.com/beberlei/composer-monorepo-plugin]Composer-Mono
       Repo-Plugin - The plugin adds support for managing dependencies for
       multiple packages in a single repository.
     * [https://github.com/netresearch/composer-patches-plugin]Composer-Pa
       tches-Plugin - Enables you to provide patches for any package from
       any package. When the dependency is fetched, the patch is applied
       on top.
     * [https://github.com/cweagans/composer-patches]Composer-Patches -
       The plugin applies a patch from a local or remote file to any
       required package.
     * [https://github.com/Webysther/composer-plugin-qa]Composer-Plugin-QA
       - Comprehensive Plugin for composer to execute PHP Quality
       assurance Tools.
     * [https://github.com/barryvdh/composer-cleanup-plugin]Composer-Clean
       up-Plugin - Removes tests & documentation folders from the vendor
       dir.
     * [https://github.com/dg/composer-cleaner]Composer-Cleaner - The tool
       removes unnecessary files and directories from the vendor
       directory.
     * [https://github.com/Letudiant/composer-shared-package-plugin]Compos
       er-Shared-Package-Plugin - Allows you to share your selected
       packages between your projects by creating symlinks.
     * [https://github.com/dg/composer-symlinker]Composer-Symlinker -
       Enables you to load some packages from different directories
       (instead of loading them from /vendor).
     * [https://github.com/hirak/prestissimo]Prestissimo - A parallel
       downloader using phpext_curl.
     * [https://github.com/jakoch/composer-fastfetch]Composer-FastFetch -
       Parallel Downloader using external download tools: Aria2.
     * [https://github.com/ngyuki/composer-curl-plugin]Composer-Curl-Plugi
       n - The plugin use phpext_curl for downloading packages.
     * [https://github.com/mnsami/composer-custom-directory-installer]Comp
       oser-Custom-Directory-Installer - A composer plugin, to install
       different types of composer packages in custom directories outside
       the default composer installation path (which is in the vendor
       folder).
     * [https://packagist.org/packages/jms/composer-deps-analyzer]Composer
       -Dependency-Analyzer - Allows you to build a dependency graph for
       an installed composer project.
     * [https://github.com/Ocramius/PackageVersions]PackageVersions -
       Provides a very quick and easy access to installed composer
       dependency versions.
     * [https://github.com/mindplay-dk/composer-locator]Composer Locator -
       Provides a means of locating the installation path for a given
       Composer package name.
     * [https://github.com/ThaDafinser/PackageInfo]PackageInfo - Check if
       a package is installed and retrieve all package informations like
       version, tag release date, description, ...
     * [https://github.com/lichunqiang/composer-ignore-plugin]composer-ign
       ore-plugin - The composer plugin to remove useless files in vendor
       by yourself.
     * [https://github.com/BrainMaestro/composer-git-hooks]composer-git-ho
       oks - A library for easily managing git hooks in your composer
       config.
     * [https://github.com/symfony/flex]Symfony-Flex - Provides
       [https://github.com/symfony/recipes]recipe-based installation and
       configuration management for Symfony packages.
     * [https://github.com/DealerDirect/phpcodesniffer-composer-installer]
       phpcodesniffer-composer-installer - Automates the configuration of
       custom PHP_CodeSniffer standards/sniffs via Composer
     * [https://github.com/jderusse/composer-warmup]Composer-Warmup - The
       plugin adds the command warmup-opcode to Composer, which triggers
       the compilation of all PHP files discovered in your project into
       the Opcache.
     * [https://github.com/fxpio/foxy]Foxy - Composer plugin that executes
       npm/yarn packages installation operations when composer package is
       installed or updated.
     * [https://github.com/thecodingmachine/nodejs-installer]nodejs-instal
       ler - downloads and installs NodeJS and npm as composer package

Tools

     * [https://semver.mwl.be/]Composer SemVer Checker - Enables you
       identify constraint to version resolution issues, by doing a
       semantic version check for Packagist hosted packages.
     * [https://github.com/igorw/composer-yaml]Composer-Yaml - This tool
       converts composer.yml to composer.json.
     * [https://github.com/franzliedke/studio]Studio - A workbench for
       developing Composer packages. Its an alternative to editing
       dependencies in the vendor folder or using
       [https://getcomposer.org/doc/05-repositories.md#path]PathRepositori
       es to load a local clone of your dependency into your project.
     * [https://github.com/OctoLinker/OctoLinker]OctoLinker Browser
       Extension - Enables you to navigate Composer/NPM dependencies on
       Github.
     * [https://github.com/maglnet/ComposerRequireChecker]ComposerRequireC
       hecker - A CLI tool to analyze dependencies and verify that no
       unknown imported symbols are used in the sources of a package.

Scripts

     * [https://github.com/raphaelstolt/composer-travis-lint]composer-trav
       is-lint - Allows you to lint the Travis CI configuration file
       (.travis.yml).
     * [https://github.com/raphaelstolt/composer-multitest]composer-multit
       est - Enables you to run a Composer script against multiple,
       locally installed PHP versions, which are managed by PHPBrew or
       phpenv.
     * [https://github.com/neronmoon/scriptsdev]ScriptsDev - Enables you
       to use a scripts-dev section, which triggers scripts only in dev
       mode.
     * [https://github.com/Incenteev/ParameterHandler]ParameterHandler -
       Allows you to manage your ignored parameters when running a
       composer install or update.
     * [https://github.com/jakoch/phantomjs-installer]PhantomJS-Installer-
       A Composer Package which installs the PhantomJS binary (Linux,
       Windows, Mac) into /bin of your project.
     * [https://github.com/tommy-muehle/tooly-composer-script]tooly -
       Manage needed PHAR files in your project composer.json. Every PHAR
       file will be saved in the composer binary directory. Optional with
       GPG verification for every PHAR.

Packagist-compatible repositories

     * [https://wpackagist.org/]WordPress Packagist - Mirrors the
       WordPress plugin and theme directories as a Composer repository.
     * [https://asset-packagist.org/]Asset Packagist - Enables
       installation of Bower and NPM packages as native Composer packages.
     * [http://packages.firegento.com/]Firegento - A Composer Repository
       providing Magento Modules.
     * [https://www.drupal.org/node/2822344]Drupal Packagist - Composer
       repositories for Drupal 7 and 8 core, modules, and themes.
     * [https://github.com/lukaszlach/satis-server]Satis Server - This
       docker container provides a Satis Server and enables you to run a
       private, self-hosted Composer repository with support for Git,
       Mercurial, and Subversion, HTTP API, HTTPs support, webhook handler
       and scheduled builds.

GUI

     * [https://www.getcomposercat.com/]Composercat - Composercat is a
       comprehensive GUI for the Composer package manager, designed both
       for professionals and people taking their first steps with
       Composer.

Tutorials

     * [https://scotch.io/tutorials/a-beginners-guide-to-composer]A
       beginners guide to Composer
     * [https://www.dev-metal.com/composer-tutorial/]A short & simple
       Composer tutorial
     * [https://code.tutsplus.com/tutorials/easy-package-management-with-c
       omposer--net-25530]Easy package management with Composer
     * [https://www.sitepoint.com/re-introducing-composer/]PHP Dependency
       Management with Composer
     * [https://daylerees.com/composer-primer/]Composer Primer
     * [https://alanstorm.com/php_composer_magento_tutorial/]PHP Composer
       Magento Tutorial by Alan Storm

